# World Cup Fantasy Draft Rules

## Competition Format

* There will be x number of participants in the competition.
* Each participant will draft a **7-player squad**.
* Players can only be selected once. Once drafted, they are unavailable to all other participants.
* The draft order will be determined before the draft begins.

## Squad Restrictions

* Each squad must contain exactly **7 players**.
* A maximum of **2 players from the same national team** may be selected.
* No duplicate players are allowed across squads.

## Scoring System

Participants earn points based on the real-life performances of their drafted players during World Cup matches.

| Event        | Points   |
| ------------ | -------- |
| Goal         | 4 Points |
| Assist       | 3 Points |
| Clean Sheet* | 3 Points |

*Clean sheet points are awarded to goalkeepers and defenders whose national team does not concede a goal in a match.

## Transfer Market

To keep the competition active throughout the tournament, a transfer window will open every **3 days**.

### Transfer Rules

* Eliminated players can be swapped for any **undrafted player** whose national team is still active in the tournament.
* Players already drafted by another manager cannot be transferred in.
* All transfers must comply with the **maximum 2 players per national team** rule.
* Transfers must be completed before the transfer window closes.
* Once a transfer is confirmed, it cannot be reversed.

## Leaderboard

* A leaderboard will be maintained throughout the tournament.
* Points earned by drafted players will be added to their manager's total score.
* The leaderboard will be updated regularly throughout the competition.

## Winning the Competition

* The participant with the highest total points at the end of the FIFA World Cup will be crowned the **World Cup Fantasy Champion**.

### Tie-Breakers

If two or more participants finish level on points:

1. Most goals scored by drafted players.
2. Most assists by drafted players.
3. Highest-scoring individual player in a squad.
4. If still tied, the title will be shared.

